results.definition: a Roman Catholic who advocates ultramontanism (supreme papal authority in matters of faith and discipline)
on or relating to or characteristic of the region or peoples beyond the Alps from Italy (or north of the Alps)

results.definition: on the Italian or Roman side of the Alps
examples: ancient cisalpine Gaul included an area south and east of the Alps
